Title: Noncommuting Gauge Fields as a Lagrange Fluid
Authors: R. Jackiw, S.-Y. Pi, A.P. Polychronakos
Comments: 19 pages; final version to appear in Annals of Physics
Report-no: MIT-CTP-3263, BUHEP-02-18, RU-02-3-B
Journal-ref: Annals Phys. 301 (2002) 157-173
\\
  The Lagrange description of an ideal fluid gives rise in a natural way to a
gauge potential and a Poisson structure that are classical precursors of
analogous noncommuting entities. With this observation we are led to construct
gauge-covariant coordinate transformations on a noncommuting space. Also we
recognize the Seiberg-Witten map from noncommuting to commuting variables as
the quantum correspondent of the Lagrange to Euler map in fluid mechanics.
